    <body>
      <head>Ludwig Rottenberg</head>
      <div>

        <p>Austrian conductor and composer.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>Born in <ref cRef="entity-002247">Bukovina</ref>, Ludwig Rottenberg studied theory and
          composition with <ref cRef="entity-000265">Robert Fuchs</ref> and <ref
            cRef="entity-000562">Eusebius Mandyczewski</ref> in Vienna. Upon the recommendation of
            <ref cRef="entity-000094">Brahms</ref> and <ref cRef="entity-000110">Bülow</ref>,
          Rottenberg was appointed Kapellmeister at the Frankfurt Opera in 1893, a position he held
          until 1926. </p>
      </div>

    </body>

